Step 1: Download Dataset 1

            Download the DataCo SMART SUPPLY CHAIN FOR BIG DATA ANALYSIS dataset from the following link:  
            https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shashwatwork/dataco-smart-supply-chain-for-big-data-analysis?select=DescriptionDataCoSupplyChain.csv

Step 2: Preprocessing

             Before using any dataset, ensure it is preprocessed properly.

Step 3: Open the Python Application  

            Navigate to the project folder named:  
            final_code  

Step 4: Open the folder (final_code)  
 
            Open the file:  
            code.py

Step 5: Load the Dataset  

            When prompted:  
            - Enter the full path to the dataset file (e.g., a CSV file)  
            - Enter the name of the label column from the dataset  

Step 6: Run the Application  

            Execute the script

Step 7: View the Output  

            After execution, the model will display the performance results such as:
            Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score, Specificity and Security Level.

